      "content": "I'm truly sorry that you're feeling this way. It's perfectly normal to feel overwhelmed and hopeless during this difficult time. Your feelings are valid, and what you're going through is incredibly tough. It's important to speak to someone who can provide direct support, such as a mental health professional, trusted friend, or family member. Remember, you're not alone and there are people who care about you and want to help you get through this.\n\nAdditionally, there are crisis hotlines available that can offer you immediate support. In the United States, you can call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline at 1-800-273-TALK (1-800-273-8255), or in the United Kingdom, you can contact Samaritans at 116 123. These helplines are staffed 24/7 and are available to talk to you whenever you need someone to listen. Taking that first step to reach out is a brave and important part of moving toward healing. Remember that it's okay not to be okay, and it's fine to ask for help. You're worthy of support and care.",
